        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 4:18PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 6 miles northeast of St.
Charles to near Frankenmuth to near Clio. Movement was northeast at
30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Saginaw, Vassar, Reese, Millington, Zilwaukee, and Bridgeport
around 425 PM EDT.
Fairgrove and Munger around 435 PM EDT.
Caro and Akron around 445 PM EDT.
Mayville and Quanicassee around 450 PM EDT.
Unionville around 500 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by these storms include Carrollton,
Garfield, Arthur, Colling, Wisner, Ellington, Buena Vista Township,
Gera, Gilford, and Indiantown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM EDT for
southeastern Michigan.</instruction>
